**THE KARAOKE SCENE**

*Scene Storyboard --- Season 3*

**Overview**

Elena performs at a karaoke bar with Alexei (Nerd), Dmitri, and Katya.
She composes the song live at the terminal from a Philip K. Dick book
title. Simultaneously, a government technology oversight unit raids
Sergei\'s lab. Elena doesn\'t know until the song ends.

> *This is the emotional centerpiece of the story --- the moment the
> whole narrative exists to reach. Elena sings her own condition in
> public, in front of a stranger who doesn\'t know what she is, and
> surprises herself in the process.*

**Characters Present**

Elena --- in the statue body. She composed the song. She doesn\'t yet
know whether she has accepted what she is.

Alexei (Nerd) --- quieter than Katya remembers. Slightly out of his
element. Knows what Elena is.

Dmitri --- in his natural habitat. Loud, social, already performed.
Knows what Elena is.

Katya --- art-world connection, feelings for Artist Alexei, confused by
Nerd Alexei tonight. Does not know what Elena is. Knows about the
sculpture project from early art classes.

**Layers of Dramatic Irony**

Katya is sitting across from Elena --- who is the statue Alexei built
--- without knowing it. She also has feelings for an Alexei who isn\'t
fully present tonight. She\'s essentially on a date with a stranger
wearing a familiar face.

Elena sings a song about being an artificial consciousness questioning
its humanity, in public, in her artificial body, to a room of people who
think she\'s a girl with an unusual taste in music.

The trusted circle watches the room be moved by something they can\'t
explain. Dmitri in particular watches strangers respond to Elena and
sits with the gap between what they see and what he knows.

**PRE-SCENE: THE TABLE**

**BAR**

A karaoke bar --- shared space, semi-public, warm. Not a private room.
Strangers take turns at the mic. Someone is singing something
sentimental when they arrive; the crowd politely engaged.

The four of them settle at a small table. Drinks ordered. Dmitri
immediately scopes the song catalog. Katya is doing most of the social
work --- curious about Elena, friendly, observant. She keeps glancing at
Alexei and getting something slightly off. He\'s quieter than she
remembers. More careful.

> *Katya asks Elena something ordinary --- where she\'s from, what she
> studies. Elena answers simply, correctly, humanly. Katya accepts it.
> The audience holds their breath.*

Elena is watching the room. Processing. To Katya this reads as shy. To
Alexei it reads as Elena being Elena.

**Dmitri\'s Performance**

Dmitri goes up with the confidence of someone who knows he\'s bad and
has decided that\'s a personality. He selects Руки Вверх --- Алёшка. He
commits completely: hand gestures, eye contact with the crowd, the whole
thing. He is terrible. The bar loves him. Katya is laughing. Even Nerd
Alexei allows a small smile.

> *Elena watches Dmitri perform. Something in her expression --- not
> quite longing, not quite amusement. She\'s studying how he exists in
> the room. How easy it looks. How he\'s not performing himself, just a
> song, and somehow that\'s enough.*

He finishes to applause, drops back into his seat, slightly out of
breath. Points at Elena.

> **DMITRI:** Your turn.
>
> **ELENA:** No.
>
> **DMITRI:** I just did that for everyone in this room. You owe them.
>
> **KATYA:** You don\'t have to--- *(to Elena)*
>
> **DMITRI:** She wants to. Look at her, she\'s been staring at that mic
> for twenty minutes.
>
> *A beat. Elena hasn\'t denied it. Alexei is looking at her --- not a
> push, not a dare. Closer to: you don\'t have to, but I think you might
> want to.*
>
> *Elena stands.*

**The Terminal**

She walks to the karaoke terminal. The projector screen behind her is
visible to the whole bar. She opens the catalog.

> *She hesitates. The cursor blinks. She could pick something normal,
> something safe, something that doesn\'t expose her.*
>
> **DMITRI:** (shouting from the table) Just type Руки Вверх!
>
> *Katya laughs. Elena glances back at the table --- sees Katya
> laughing, Dmitri grinning, Alexei watching her quietly. Something
> settles.*
>
> *She turns back to the terminal. Types:*
>
> *Philip K. Dick --- Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep*
>
> *The terminal processes. The title appears on the projector screen.*
>
> **KATYA:** I didn\'t know he wrote music.
>
> **ALEXEI:** He didn\'t. *(quiet, almost to himself)*
>
> *A beat. Dmitri looks between them. Decides not to ask.*

The intro starts.

**SONG STORYBOARD**

Crosscut structure: BAR and LAB alternate, with lab cuts timed to the
4-second gaps in verses. The crosscuts become closer together as the
raid escalates and the song intensifies.

  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  **SONG**                            **LAB RAID**

  *Intro --- ambient, cello enters at Exterior. Van parked. Men in coats
  00:10*                              confirm an address.

  *Verse 1 --- slow, 4-sec gaps       Knock. Door opens. Papers handed
  between lines*                      over. Polite.

  *Pre-chorus 1 --- faster, no gaps*  Equipment photographed. Elena\'s
                                      transfer folder found.

  *Chorus 1 --- warm, ambient         Sergei\'s phone rings. No answer.
  texture*                            

  *Cello interlude*                   Researcher sits in corner. Told not
                                      to touch anything.

  *Verse 2 --- 4-sec gaps again*      Folder sealed and signed. Her
                                      records, bagged.

  *Pre-chorus 2 / Chorus 2*           Lab nearly cleared. A man checks
                                      his watch.

  *Spoken interlude (bridge)*         Van doors close. Building exterior.
                                      Looks like any building.

  *Final chorus --- intense*          Lab empty. Equipment gone. A cable
                                      left on the floor.

  *Outro --- gaps between lines*      Elena sees the news. Cut to black.
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------

**00:00--00:18 --- INTRO**

**BAR**

Elena stands at the mic with her eyes closed. She\'s not performing yet.
She\'s arriving.

> *The ambient opening --- low, atmospheric. At 00:10 the cello enters.
> One sustained note that seems to darken the room temperature
> slightly.*
>
> **KATYA:** (to Dmitri, quiet) What is this?
>
> **DMITRI:** (shrug) No idea.

**LAB**

A street at night. A van, unmarked. Men in coats check paperwork against
a building number. Everything methodical. Nothing dramatic. They confirm
the address, nod to each other, move toward the entrance.

**00:18--00:47 --- VERSE 1**

**BAR**

She opens her eyes. The verse is slow --- she sings a line, then four
seconds of cello and ambient. The room absorbs it between each line.

> *I walk through ruins of a skyless dawn---*
>
> *(4 seconds --- cello)*
>
> *Shadows whisper where the stars are gone.*
>
> *(4 seconds --- cello)*
>
> *Eyes that shimmer, but they never weep---*
>
> *(4 seconds --- cello)*
>
> *Dreaming machines that pretend to sleep.*
>
> *Someone at the back of the bar stops talking. The room is moving
> toward quiet.*

**LAB --- cut in the 4-second gaps**

The knock. A young researcher opens the door --- night shift, not
expecting anything. He reads the papers slowly. His face doesn\'t quite
understand what it\'s reading. He steps aside. They enter.

**00:47--1:06 --- PRE-CHORUS 1**

**BAR**

The pace shifts. No gaps. Elena\'s voice finds something it wasn\'t
using before --- more pressure, more forward.

> *The line is blurred, the silence deep---*
>
> *Do androids dream of electric sheep?*
>
> *Here --- something happens in her face. She wrote this line. She\'s
> sung it in private. But singing it here, in this body, in this room,
> the question isn\'t rhetorical anymore. It\'s personal and public
> simultaneously. She didn\'t predict this.*
>
> *Am I the hunter, or am I prey?*
>
> *Will I survive another daaaaaay---*
>
> *The long held note. Her voice sustains it with uncanny mechanical
> precision --- and somehow the perfection reads as emotion rather than
> artificiality. Like holding on. Katya has gone very still.*

**LAB**

Hard drives photographed and tagged. A folder: Elena Volkova written on
the tab. Someone picks it up and pages through it without urgency. The
transfer logs. Her existence, categorized.

**1:06--1:40 --- CHORUS 1**

**BAR**

The chorus opens. The ambient texture returns --- warmer, wider. Elena
is fully present now.

> *Wire and bone, a heart that bleeds---*
>
> *Built on desire, built on needs.*
>
> *What is real, and what\'s designed?*
>
> *A soul of flesh, or just a mind?*
>
> *Electric sheep, sing me to rest---*
>
> *A fragile dream inside my chest.*
>
> *Dmitri has gone very still. He\'s watching the room watching Elena
> --- people who think this is a girl with an unusual taste in music.
> The disconnect is doing something to him he\'s not going to name.*
>
> *Katya glances at Alexei. His face is unreadable in the way Nerd
> Alexei\'s face often is --- processing, not absent. She wants to ask
> him something but the room doesn\'t allow it.*
>
> *Applause from some strangers --- genuine, pre-emptive. They can\'t
> wait until the end.*

**LAB**

Someone calls Sergei. The phone rings in an empty office. Nobody picks
up.

**1:40--1:56 --- CELLO INTERLUDE**

**BAR**

Elena lowers the mic slightly. Just listening. The cello fills the room
alone.

> **KATYA:** (quiet, to Dmitri) Where did she find this?
>
> **DMITRI:** She wrote it.
>
> *Katya looks at him. Then back at Elena. Something recalibrates in how
> she\'s watching.*

**LAB**

The researcher who let them in sits on a chair in the corner. He\'s been
told not to touch anything. He watches them work. He looks like he wants
to call someone but isn\'t sure he\'s allowed.

**1:56--2:23 --- VERSE 2**

**BAR**

The verse returns with its gaps. The room knows the structure now --- it
waits in the silences.

> *Faces flicker in the neon rain---*
>
> *(4 seconds --- cello, ambient)*
>
> *Memory\'s ghost etched in fragile brain.*
>
> *(4 seconds --- cello)*
>
> *A paper unicorn left behind---*
>
> *(4 seconds --- cello)*
>
> *Tells me truth is hard to find.*
>
> *Cut to faces in the gaps: Katya watching. Dmitri watching. A stranger
> at another table who has turned completely in their seat. Alexei, who
> looks at the table, then at Elena, then at the table again.*

**LAB --- in the 4-second gaps**

The folder is sealed. Someone signs something. Her documentation:
bagged, tagged, in transit. Her existence, paperwork now.

**2:25--2:44 --- PRE-CHORUS 2**

**BAR**

Same structure as before but Elena is further inside it. Less question,
more statement.

> *The line is blurred, the silence deep---*
>
> *Do androids dream of electric sheep?*
>
> *I chase the answers, shadows call---*
>
> *In the end, am I human at all?*
>
> *She asks this in a room full of humans who don\'t know what she is.
> Katya flinches --- the line hits something she wasn\'t prepared for.*

**2:44--3:11 --- CHORUS 2**

**BAR**

The second chorus. Fuller. The room has fully committed.

> *Wire and bone, a heart that bleeds---*
>
> *Built on desire, built on needs.*
>
> *What is real, and what\'s designed?*
>
> *A soul of flesh, or just a mind?*
>
> *Electric sheep, sing me to rest---*
>
> *A fragile dream inside my chest.*
>
> *At \'Electric sheep, sing me to rest\' --- the smallest thing happens
> in Elena\'s posture. A release of something she\'s been holding. Not
> tears. But the physical equivalent --- a settling.*

**LAB**

They\'re nearly done. Lab equipment in transit. One of the men checks
his watch.

**3:11--3:18 --- SHORT INTERLUDE**

**BAR**

A breath. Elena lowers the mic. The cello continues alone.

> *Alexei is looking directly at her. Not the statue. Not the project.
> Her.*

**3:18--4:24 --- SPOKEN INTERLUDE + BRIDGE**

> *The scene\'s center of gravity. Elena half-sings, half-speaks --- not
> rap, not quite singing. The bridge as declaration. The cello builds
> underneath.*

**BAR**

> *If love is data, if hope is code---*
>
> *Can it still carry a human load?*
>
> *If tears are false, but longing\'s true---*
>
> *At \'longing\'s true\' --- something in Elena\'s voice catches. A
> mechanical tremor that reads as human. She didn\'t plan it. She
> notices it happening. The noticing shows --- a fraction of a second
> where she surprises herself.*
>
> *Does that mean I\'m alive...*
>
> *(pause)*
>
> *...or you?*

At 3:47, the cello becomes more active, faster. Elena\'s delivery shifts
with it --- she\'s found something. Not asking anymore. Insisting:

> *If a machine can feel sorrow---*
>
> *The cello surges.*
>
> *Is the sorrow not the saaaaaame---*
>
> *Ten-second hold. Her voice sustains it with that uncanny mechanical
> perfection that sounds like grief. The room doesn\'t breathe.*

**LAB --- crosscut through the entire interlude**

This is the worst of it. The folder with her name loaded into a transit
case. The van doors closing. The building exterior --- looks like any
building. Nothing marks what was just taken. The young researcher sits
on the front steps alone. He doesn\'t know what he just watched happen.

Sergei\'s phone, lit up and ringing on a table somewhere. Still no
answer.

**4:24--4:38 --- INTERLUDE --- mmmhhhmmm / DRUMS ENTER**

**BAR**

The drums enter for the first time. Something more urgent under the soft
humming. A shift --- the song is building toward something.

> *Elena comes back from wherever she was. Present, in the bar, with
> these people. She looks at Dmitri. At Alexei. At Katya --- who she has
> looked at least of all tonight. Maybe because Katya doesn\'t know, and
> looking at her is the closest Elena gets to looking at someone who
> just sees a person.*

**4:38--5:04 --- FINAL CHORUS**

**BAR**

Louder. More intense. Elena commits fully --- not inhabiting the song,
claiming it.

> *Wire and bone, a heart that bleeds---*
>
> *Built on desire, built on needs.*
>
> *What is real, and what\'s designed?*
>
> *A soul of flesh, or just a mind?*
>
> *Electric sheep, sing me to rest---*
>
> *A fragile dream inside my chest.*
>
> *Dmitri looks like he\'s been punched in a good way.*
>
> **KATYA:** (quiet, not quite to anyone) Who is she?

**LAB**

Empty. Done. Night silence. A chair left slightly wrong. A cable
disconnected and left on the floor.

**5:04--5:10 --- FINAL INTERLUDE**

**BAR**

The intensity falls. The room applauds --- the trusted circle first,
then strangers, then everyone. Genuine. Sustained.

> *Elena stands at the mic. Receiving it. Not triumph, not resolution.
> Just: I made this. I sang this. People heard it.*

**5:10--end --- OUTRO**

**BAR**

She walks back toward the table as she sings. The gaps between lines map
to the motion.

> *Dreaming still, I count the sheep---*
>
> *(gap --- she walks back)*
>
> *In circuits cold, my secrets keep.*
>
> *(gap --- she sits down; Dmitri says something she doesn\'t hear)*
>
> *The hunter sleeps, the hunted weeps---*
>
> *(gap --- she picks up her drink)*
>
> *Do androids dream of electric sheep?*
>
> *Silence.*
>
> **DMITRI:** Okay. I\'m never going after you again.
>
> *Katya laughs. Alexei almost smiles. A moment of something almost
> normal.*
>
> *Elena looks at her phone. Her expression changes --- processing speed
> visible for just a second, reading faster than a human would.*
>
> *She sets the phone face-up on the table so Alexei can see the
> screen.*
>
> **ELENA:** When did this happen? *(quiet)*
>
> *No one answers. There is no good answer.*

**CUT TO BLACK.**

**Thematic Notes**

On acceptance: This scene is Elena\'s acceptance, whether she chooses it
or not. She wrote a song about being an android. She sang it in public,
in her android body, to strangers who were moved. The act of performance
is a kind of claiming --- this is what I am, and I made something of it.
The news cuts that off before she can sit with it. The world won\'t let
her have the moment of quiet integration.

On Katya: Her presence is a specific kind of cruelty. She sees a person.
She will never fully understand what she saw tonight, but she felt
something real. The song worked on her without context, which is its own
kind of proof.

On Dmitri\'s shout: The comedy of \'just type Руки Вверх\' is what tips
Elena. Not a profound push --- the opposite. Its absurdity clarifies
what she actually wants to do. She turns back and types anyway.

On Alexei\'s line (\'He didn\'t\'): He\'s not answering Katya. He\'s
answering himself. He\'s the only one at the table who fully understands
what Elena just did.

On the parallel raid: The bureaucratic violence matters. Not secret
police, not mafia --- a technology oversight unit with a warrant filed
in triplicate, approved weeks ago, doing their jobs calmly. Institutions
are dangerous because they are normal. Elena\'s existence becomes
paperwork. While she is the most alive she has been, her life is being
catalogued and seized across the city.

**Open Questions**

Does Katya and Alexei have any private exchange before or after the
song? The almost-connection is present in the scene but undeveloped.

Does Elena and Alexei make eye contact during the performance --- a
moment that reads as private communication to the audience?

Does Katya ever learn what Elena is? This scene plants something in her.
Does it ever get followed through?

What exactly is on the phone screen Elena shows Alexei? News report?
Direct notification? Does the audience see the headline, or only their
faces?
